Data Cleaning¶

We are not planning to develop any analysis related to:¶

  • 'imdb_id' Because we already have and ID column to use
  • 'cast' We are no interested in perform any text analysis on this variable
  • 'homepage' This column has a los of NaN values, so we prefer not to use it
  • 'tagline' We are nos interested to perform a text analysis in this variable
  • 'keywords' Same argument used in the tagline column
  • 'overview' Same argument related to the text analysis
  • 'budget_adj' We have the budget column to perforn analysis related to that
  • 'revenue_adj' We have the revenue column to perform the analysis related to that
  • 'relase_date' We could use the realse month if we plan to do some analysis related to the date

#we can also clasify a movie based on their popularity score
size_range_pop = round((max_pop - min_pop)/5)
size_range_pop

def get_pop(row):    
    if row >= 0 and row < 653:
        return "Not popular"
    elif row >= 653 and row < 1306:
        return "Kinda not popular"
    elif row >= 1306 and row < 1959:
        return "Half Popular"
    elif row >= 1959 and row < 2612:
        return "Popular"
    elif row >= 2612 and row < 3270:
        return "Really popular"
    
movies_f["Clasification"] = movies_f["weighted_popularity"].apply(get_pop)

Question 2: How the director is related with the budget, revenue,popularity and the number of movies ?¶

In [136]:
def make_autopct(values):
    def my_autopct(pct):
        total = sum(values)
        val = int(round(pct*total/100.0))
        return '{v:d}'.format(v=val)
    return my_autopct

#Top 5 directors 
director_movie =movies_f.groupby(["director"])["original_title"].count()
director_movie.sort_values(ascending = False)
Top5_Directors = director_movie.sort_values(ascending = False).iloc[0:5]

plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 20
plt.title("Top 5 Directors  ")
plt.xlabel("Number of movies per director")


Top5_Directors.plot(kind = 'pie',figsize = (8,8), autopct=make_autopct(Top5_Directors));

Conclusions¶

- The best
    -- The movie with the biggest budget (425.000.000 USD) is The Warrior's Way by SngMoo Lee. 
    -- The movie with the biggest revenue(2.781.505.847 USD) is Avatar by James Cameron
    -- The movie with the biggest popularity on IMDB is Inception by Christopher Nolan

- The Worst
    -- There are 5636 movies that does not have budget.        
    -- There are 5952 movies that does not have budget. 
    -- The movie with the smallest popularity on IMDB is Transmorphers by Leigh Scott

- Genres
    -- The most popular genre is the Adventure, while the less popular is Foreign
    -- The most expensive genre is Adventure, while the less expensive is Foreign
    -- The genre that won the most money is Adventure, while the less succesful is foreign

- Directors
    -- The director that has directed most movies is Woody Allen
    -- The directors that made the most popular movies is Don Hall and Chris Williams
    -- the director that spents the most on budget is Sngmoo Lee
    -- The directors that won the most with their movies is Kyla Balda and Pierre Coffin

-Correlation
    -- As expected the popularity is positively correlated with the revenue. So we can assume that a popular movies sells better
    -- The runtime is negatively correlated with the year of release. So we can assume that older movies were shorter than new ones

The minimum budget and revenue situation could mean that they start as a free budget/revenue movie or the data is incomplete. in this case we are goingt to asume the second option.
